        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 7:11PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 710 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
South Branch, or 9 miles west of Wyalusing, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Towanda, Wysox, Wilmot, Hollenback, Wyalusing, Monroe, Laceyville,
New Albany, Overton, and Monroeton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
